
Problem Statement:
Unmonitored garbage bins often overflow, causing health and
hygiene issues in urban areas.
Objective:
Develop an IoT system that monitors garbage bin levels using an
ultrasonic sensor and sends alerts when the bin is full.
Requirements:
NodeMCU or ESP32
Ultrasonic Sensor (HC-SR04)
Jumper wires, breadboard
Battery pack
IoT dashboard (Blynk/ThingSpeak)
Expected Outcome:
A real-time smart waste management prototype that alerts
municipal teams to clean full bins, improving urban cleanliness.

